horizons was founded in  by massachusettsbased bright horizons linda a mason and roger h brown bright horizons operates more than  child care centers worldwide more than  across the us and more than  in the uk and ireland the company also operates centers in canada and puerto rico bright horizons acquired kidsunlimited in april  which has  nurseries and a successful childcare vouchers business this development means that bright horizons now serves around  children and families the advisory board includes scholars and practitioners such as ed schein and stew friedman the company was publicly traded on the nasdaq under the ticker symbol bfam until it was acquired by bain capital in may  and became publicly traded again  in  bright horizons family solutions was named for the fifteenth time to fortune magazines annual  best places to work in america in  the senior leadership team at bright horizons formed the bright horizons foundation for children through the foundation bright horizons supports nonprofit organizations with a focus on programs for children and families the foundation is headquartered in brentwood tennessee bright spaces the foundation’s program creates play rooms for children in crisis in partnerships with bright horizons’ clients other nonprofits city governments and other organizations referencesedit  child care information exchange  executive team bright horizons family services retrieved    corporate information kidsunlimited retrieved    httpmoneycnncommagazinesfortunebestcompaniessnapshotshtmliidbcfllist  child care information exchange external linksedit company website this article about a corporation in the service industry is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlebrighthorizonsfamilysolutionsoldid categories child care companiescompanies listed on the new york stock exchangeservice company stubshidden categories all stub articles navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontr